  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Zambia: radioeins (rbb) is reversing deforestation</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Zambia&apos;s Copperbelt region, native Miombo woodlands have been disappearing for decades. WeForest is engaging with and training hundreds of small-scale farmers to restore these forests. In doing so, the farmers benefit from diversified livelihood sources, higher incomes and new skills! Besides, via the project&apos;s holistic approach, farmers receive help in obtaining land ownership.  With the support of radioeins (rbb), WeForest is restoring those degraded landscapes.</narrative>
  </description>
